quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  10,103,"Then We will save Our messengers and those who have believed. Thus, it is an obligation upon Us that We save the believers.{1}",footnotes:1:From Allāh's punishment.
  10,104,"Say, [O Muḥammad], "
  10,105,"And [commanded], 'Direct your face [i.e., self] toward the religion, inclining to truth, and never be of those who associate others with Allāh;"
  11,70,"But when he saw their hands not reaching for it, he distrusted them and felt from them apprehension.{1} They said, ",footnotes:1:Traditionally, if a guest refused to eat, it meant that he harbored ill will toward the host or intended him harm.
  11,71,"And his wife was standing, and she smiled.{1} Then We gave her good tidings of Isaac and after Isaac, Jacob.",footnotes:1:In pleasure at the news of the forthcoming punishment of the evil people who denied Prophet Lot (upon him be peace).
  11,72,"She said, ",footnotes:1:An expression of surprise and amazement.
  12,31,"So when she heard of their scheming, she sent for them and prepared for them a banquet and gave each one of them a knife and said [to Joseph], ",footnotes:1:So distracted were they at the sight of him.In His ability to create such beauty.
  12,32,"She said, "
  12,33,"He said, "